Installation:
- Install Python modules pywbem and pyzabbix
- Copy files to appropriate locations, check paths in scripts

/etc/zabbix/externalscripts: (zabbix scripts)
 svc_perf (chmod +x)
 svc_perf_discovery (chmod +x)
 svc_perf_discovery.py
 svc_perf_wbem.py
 svc_perf_graph.py
 svc_perf_graph (chmod +x)
 svc_perf.conf (configuration file)

/etc/cron.d: (statistics polling script)
 svc_perf_cron

/var/cache/zabbix: (script-created cache files, must be persistent, rw access for zabbix user)
 svc_perf.XXX.cache
 svc_perf.XXX.errlog

- Import template to Zabbix from file _Special_Storwize_Perf.xml
- Create node with DNS name/IP address pointing to Storwize BLOCK module mgmt interface, link template _Special_Storwize_Perf
- Create Zabbix account with admin permissions to Storwize nodes for use by svc_perf_graph
- Connect to Storwize V7000 block module with SSH and run command:
 startstats -interval 3
It will change internal Storwize stats collection interval to practical value, default is too long - 15 minutes. 
This interval must correspond to cron schedule in /etc/cron.d/svc_perf_cron
- Wait some time for Zabbix to call discovery script and add items to node
- Cron will run svc_perf script periodically and feed stats to Zabbix, svc_perf_graph script will generate summary graphs by pool
